2026-04-16 07:53:07 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control module 1 Indicator LED', 'Control module 2 Indicator LED', 'Control module 3 Indicator LED', 'Control module 4 Indicator LED', 'Control module 5 Indicator LED', 'Control module 6 Indicator LED', 'Control module 7 Indicator LED', 'Control module 8 Indicator LED'] hypothesis_explanation='All of the control module indicator LEDs, along with their associated resistors, have been physically removed from the system (as stated in the results of the direct inspection and attempted voltage measurement). Since these LEDs and resistors are connected in parallel with the series circuit, their absence creates an open circuit at each control module position—even if the switches are ON, there is no current path through each module. Thus, the circuit as a whole is open and the lamp cannot turn on. The root cause is the missing LED-resistor pairs in all control modules. Replacing these components should restore circuit continuity and normal operation.'
